MultiPixel Political Server Requirements
Version 1.0 — Relimintor (Raptor4 / MultiPixel)

1. APPROVAL REQUIRED
Political Servers may only operate with explicit written approval from MultiPixel.

2. CLEAR LABELING
The server must display:
“This is a Political Server. Political discussion is allowed.”

3. AGE RESTRICTIONS
Server must enforce age restrictions appropriate to the political content.

4. MODERATION REQUIREMENTS
• Active moderation team required.
• Moderators must be identifiable.
• Moderators must enforce MultiPixel Community Guidelines.
• Moderators must remove illegal, extremist, or harmful content.

5. LOGGING REQUIREMENTS
Servers must maintain:
• Chat logs
• Join/leave logs
• Moderation actions

Logs must be retained for at least 90 days.

6. TRANSPARENCY
Server rules must be publicly visible and include:
• Political nature of the server
• Age restrictions
• Moderation policies
• Data collection practices

7. PROHIBITED CONTENT
Political Servers may NOT host:
• Extremist propaganda
• Terrorist content
• Calls for violence
• Hate speech
• Doxxing or harassment
• Illegal political activity

8. MULTIPIXEL OVERSIGHT
MultiPixel may:
• Request logs
• Request moderation reports
• Require rule changes
• Revoke approval at any time

9. MONETIZATION
Political Servers must follow all monetization rules in License 2.2.

10. TERMINATION
Failure to comply results in immediate revocation of approval.
